State MSM Profile: Hawaii

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Hawaii

An estimated 15,411 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Hawaii in 2013, representing 0.3% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 534,961 adult men of Hawaii, 2.9% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was less than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Hawaii resided in counties within medium or small metropolitan areas (74.3%). No MSM in Hawaii resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Hawaii, 2013

MSM in Hawaii Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Hawaii, Honolulu County had the largest population of MSM at 10,181, representing 66.1% of all MSM in the state. Kauai County had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Hawaii at 5.0%. This was greater than the percentage for Hawaii as a whole, which was 2.9% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Hawaii Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Urban Honolulu Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Urban Honolulu MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Hawaii at 10,181, or 66.1% of all MSM in the state. Of the 376,424 adult men in Urban Honolulu, an estimated 2.7% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Kahului-Wailuku-Lahaina Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Kahului-Wailuku-Lahaina MSA had a population of 1,263 MSM, or 8.2% of all MSM in Hawaii. Of the 60,388 adult men in Kahului-Wailuku-Lahaina, an estimated 2.1% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
